references: Recommendation Unlearning. Various methods for unlearning have been explored in different types of recommender systems as summarized in Table 10. For collaborative filtering, Caboose [37] incrementally adjusts the user-item matrices and re-calculates similarities only for affected entries to reflect the removal of a specific interaction. This approach avoids complete re-computation, effectively conserving computational resources.
